  "notes": [
    "The Physics/B.A. major is intended to provide a strong background in physics, yet allows students flexibility for study in other fields as well. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One and half years of Calculus through Multivariable, One course in Linear Algebra, One year of Calculus Based Physics with Lab for the major (mechanics, electricity, and magnetism). One course of General Chemistry, one course in Differential Equations, and one course in Computer Programming is Strongly Recommended . It is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED that all major prep be completed prior to transfer. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// pa.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed."
